      "ctics\ntheorem getElem_flatten_aux₂ (L : List (List α)) (i : Nat) (h : i < L.flatten.length) :\n    let j := (L.map length).partialSums.findIdx (· > i) - 1\n    have hj : j < L.length := getElem_flatten_aux₁ L i h\n    let k := i - (L.take j).flatten.length\n    k < L[j].length := sorry  -- This is the problematic `sorry`\n```\n\nThe `sorry` is supposed to prove `k < L[j].length`.\nLet's look at the relevant variables:\n- `j := (L.map length).partialSums.findIdx (· > i) - 1`\n- `k := i - (L.take j).flatten.length`\n\nThe problem is that we don't have enough information to prove `k < L[j].length` directly from the context. The proof of `getElem_flatten_aux₂` needs more intermediate steps or lemmas to establish this inequality.\n\nThe strategy of the proof seems to be:\n1.  `j := findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i)) (map length L).partialSums - 1`: This defines `j` based on the `findIdx` of a condition in `(map length L).partialSums`.\n2.  `hj := @List.getElem_flatten_aux₁ α L i h`: This is a hypothesis `j < L.length`.\n3.  `k := i - (L.take j).flatten.length`: This defines `k` based on `i` and the length of `(L.take j).flatten`.\n4.  The goal is `k < L[j].length`.\n\nThis strategy is plausible, but the jump from `j < L.length` to `k < L[j].length` is too large for the current context. We need more lemmas to bridge this gap.\n\nWe need to establish `k < L[j].length`.\nGiven:\n- `k := i - (L.take j).flatten.length`\n- `j := (L.map length).partialSums.findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i)) - 1`\n- `hj : j < L.length`\n- `h : i < L.flatten.length`\n\nWe need to show `i - (L.take j).flatten.length < L[j].length`.\n\nLet's try to establish this.\nFirst, let's note that `j` is the index such that `(L.map length).partialSums[j+1] > i` (if we adjust for 0-indexing). The definition of `j` is `findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i)) (map length L).partialSums - 1`. Let's assume the list is `P = (map length L).partialSums`. Then `j = P.findIdx (fun x => x > i) - 1`. This means `P[j+1] > i` (if `j+1 < P.length`). Also, `P[j] ≤ i` (if `j < P.length`).\n\nLet's think about the relationship between `j` and `i`.\nFrom the definition of `j`:\n- `j < P.length` (i.e., `j < (map length L).partialSums.length`)\n- `P[j+1] > i` (if `j+1 < P.length`)\n- `P[j] ≤ i` (if `j < P.length`)\n\nAlso, `P = (map length L).partialSums`. So `P[k] = (L.take k).flatten.length` for `k < P.length`. This is `getElem?_partialSums`.\n\nSo, `P[j] = (L.take j).flatten.length` (if `j < P.length`)\nAnd `P[j+1] = (L.take (j+1)).flatten.length` (if `j+1 < P.length`)\n\nWe need to show `k < L[j].length`, i.e., `i - (L.take j).flatten.length < L[j].length`.\nLet's rewrite `k` using `P[j]`:\n`k = i - P[j]`\n\nSo we need to show `i - P[j] < L[j].length`.\n\nLet's use the properties of `P`:\n- `P[j] = (L.take j).flatten.length`\n- `P[j+1] = (L.take (j+1)).flatten.length`\n- `P[j+1] = P[j] + L[j].length` (if `j < L.length`)\n\nFrom the definition of `j`:\n- `P[j] ≤ i` (if `j < P.length`)\n- `P[j+1] > i` (if `j+1 < P.length`)\n\nSo, `P[j] ≤ i < P[j+1]`.\nSubstituting the definition of `P[j+1]`:\n`P[j] ≤ i < P[j] + L[j].length`\n\nFrom `i < P[j] + L[j].length`, we get `i - P[j] < L[j].length`.\nSince `k = i - P[j]`, we get `k < L[j].length`.\n\nSo we need to formalize this reasoning.\n\nWe need to add lemmas to establish these facts.\n\n```tactics\nimport Mathlib\n\n/-! List operations -/\nnoncomputable def length (l : List α) : Nat := l.length\nnoncomputable def head (l : List α) (h : l ≠ []) : α := l.head h\nnoncomputable def getLast (l : List α) (h : l ≠ []) : α := l.getLast h\nnoncomputable def getElem (l : List α) (i : Nat) (h : i < l.length) : α := l.getElem i h\nnoncomputable def getElem? (l : List α) (i : Nat) : Option α := l.getElem? i\nnoncomputable def take (l : List α) (i : Nat) : List α := l.take i\nnoncomputable def reverse (l : List α) : List α := l.reverse\nnoncomputable def map (f : α → β) (l : List α) : List β := l.map f\nnoncomputable def foldl (f : α → β → α) (b : α) (l : List β) : α := l.foldl f b\nnoncomputable def foldr (f : α → β → β) (b : β) (l : List α) : β := l.foldr f b\nnoncomputable def partialSums (l : List α) : List α := l.partialSums\nnoncomputable def partialProds (l : List α) : List α := l.partialProds\nnoncomputable def flatten (l : List (List α)) : List α := l.flatten\n\n/-! Theorems about List operations -/\n@[simp]\ntheorem length_nil : length [] = 0 := rfl\n@[simp]\ntheorem length_cons : length (a :: l) = 1 + length l := rfl\n@[simp]\ntheorem head_nil {a} : head [] (by simp) = a := rfl\n@[simp]\ntheorem head_cons : head (a :: l) _ = a := rfl\n@[simp]\ntheorem getLast_nil {a} : getLast [] (by simp) = a := rfl\n@[simp]\ntheorem getLast_cons : getLast (a :: l) _ = l.getLast (by simp) := rfl\n@[simp]\ntheorem getElem_nil {a i} (h : i < 0) : getElem [] i h = a := rfl\n@[simp]\ntheorem getElem_cons : getElem (a :: l) i (by simp) = if i = 0 then a else getElem l (i - 1) (by omega) := rfl\n@[simp]\ntheorem getElem?_nil : getElem? [] i = none := rfl\n@[simp]\ntheorem getElem?_cons : getElem? (a :: l) i = some a if i = 0 else getElem? l (i - 1) := rfl\n@[simp]\ntheorem take_nil : take [] i = [] := rfl\n@[simp]\ntheorem take_cons : take (a :: l) i = if i = 0 then [a] else a :: take l (i - 1) := rfl\n@[simp]\ntheorem reverse_nil : reverse [] = [] := rfl\n@[simp]\ntheorem reverse_cons : reverse (a :: l) = reverse l ++ [a] := rfl\n@[simp]\ntheorem map_nil : map f [] = [] := rfl\n@[simp]\ntheorem map_cons : map f (a :: l) = f a :: map f l := rfl\n@[simp]\ntheorem foldl_nil : foldl f b [] = b := rfl\n@[simp]\ntheorem foldl_cons : foldl f b (a :: l) = f (foldl f b l) a := rfl\n@[simp]\ntheorem foldr_nil : foldr f b [] = b := rfl\n@[simp]\ntheorem foldr_cons : foldr f b (a :: l) = f a (foldr f b l) := rfl\n@[simp]\ntheorem partialSums_nil : partialSums [] = [0] := rfl\n@[simp]\ntheorem partialSums_cons : partialSums (a :: l) = 0 :: l.partialSums.map (a + ·) := rfl\n@[simp]\ntheorem partialProds_nil : partialProds [] = [1] := rfl\n@[simp]\ntheorem partialProds_cons : partialProds (a :: l) = 1 :: l.partialProds.map (a * ·) := rfl\n@[simp]\ntheorem flatten_nil : flatten [] = [] := rfl\n@[simp]\ntheorem flatten_cons : flatten (l₁ :: l₂) = l₁ ++ l₂.flatten := rfl\n\n/-! Theorems about List properties -/\ntheorem length_append : length (l₁ ++ l₂) = length l₁ + length l₂ := rfl\ntheorem length_reverse : length (l.reverse) = length l := rfl\ntheorem length_map : length (l.map f) = length l := rfl\ntheorem length_foldl : length (l.foldl f b) = length l + 1 := rfl\ntheorem length_foldr : length (l.foldr f b) = length l + 1 := rfl\ntheorem length_partialSums : length (l.partialSums) = length l + 1 := rfl\ntheorem length_partialProds : length (l.partialProds) = length l + 1 := rfl\ntheorem length_flatten : length (l.flatten) = (l.map length).sum := rfl\n\n/-! Theorems about List access -/\ntheorem head_reverse {l} : (l.reverse).head (by simp) = l.getLast (by simp) := by\n  simp [reverse_cons, head_cons, getLast_cons]\ntheorem head_foldr {f b l} (h : l ≠ []) : (l.foldr f b).head h = f (l.head h) b := by\n  simp [foldr, head_cons, head_nil]\ntheorem head_foldl {f b l} (h : l ≠ []) : (l.foldl f b).head h = f b (l.head h) := by\n  simp [foldl, head_cons, head_nil]\ntheorem head_partialSums {l} : (l.partialSums).head (by simp) = l.length := by\n  simp [partialSums, head_cons]\ntheorem head_partialProds {l} : (l.partialProds).head (by simp) = l.length := by\n  simp [partialProds, head_cons]\ntheorem head_flatten {l} : (l.flatten).head (by simp) = l.head (by simp) := by\n  simp [flatten_cons, head_cons, head_nil]\n\ntheorem getLast_reverse {f b l} : (l.reverse).getLast (by simp) = l.head (by simp) := by\n  simp [reverse_cons, getLast_cons, head_cons, head_nil]\ntheorem getLast_foldr {f b l} (h : l ≠ []) : (l.foldr f b).getLast h = f (l.getLast h) b := by\n  simp [foldr, getLast_cons, getLast_nil]\ntheorem getLast_foldl {f b l} (h : l ≠ []) : (l.foldl f b).getLast h = f b (l.getLast h) := by\n  simp [foldl, getLast_cons, getLast_nil]\ntheorem getLast_partialSums {f b l} : (l.partialSums).getLast (by simp) = l.sum := by\n  simp [partialSums, getLast_cons, foldl, sum_cons]\ntheorem getLast_partialProds {f b l} : (l.partialProds).getLast (by simp) = l.prod := by\n  simp [partialProds, getLast_cons, foldr, prod_cons]\ntheorem getLast_flatten {f b l} : (l.flatten).getLast (by simp) = l.prod := by\n  simp [flatten_cons, getLast_cons, getLast_nil]\n\ntheorem getElem_reverse {f b l i} (h : i < (l.reverse).length) : (l.reverse)[i] = l.getElem (length l - 1 - i) (by omega) := by\n  simp [reverse_cons, getElem_cons, getElem_nil, length_cons]\n  induction l generalizing i with\n  | nil => simp\n  | cons x xs ih =>\n    cases i with\n    | zero => simp [getElem_cons]\n    | succ i =>\n      simp [ih, getElem_cons]\n      all_goals omega\ntheorem getElem_foldr {f b l i} (h : i < (l.foldr f b).length) : (l.foldr f b)[i] = foldr f b (l.drop i) := by\n  induction l generalizing i with\n  | nil => simp\n  | cons x xs ih => cases i <;> simp [ih] at h ⊢\ntheorem getElem_foldl {f b l i} (h : i < (l.foldl f b).length) : (l.foldl f b)[i] = foldl f b (l.drop i) := by\n  induction l generalizing i with\n  | nil => simp\n  | cons x xs ih => cases i <;> simp [ih] at h ⊢\ntheorem getElem_partialSums {f b l i} (h : i < (l.partialSums).length) : (l.partialSums)[i] = (l.take i).sum := by\n  simp [partialSums, getElem_cons, sum_cons]\ntheorem getElem_partialProds {f b l i} (h : i < (l.partialProds).length) : (l.partialProds)[i] = (l.take i).prod := by\n  simp [partialProds, getElem_cons, prod_cons]\ntheorem getElem_flatten {f b l i} (h : i < (l.flatten).length) : (l.flatten)[i] = l.getElem (findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i)) (map length l).partialSums - 1) (by\n    have h1 : findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i)) (map length l).partialSums ≤ (map length l).partialSums.length := by\n      apply findIdx_le\n    have h2 : (map length l).partialSums.length = l.length + 1 := rfl\n    have h3 : findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i)) (map length l).partialSums ≤ l.length + 1 := by\n      omega\n    have h4 : findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i)) (map length l).partialSums - 1 < l.length := by\n      omega\n    omega\n) := by\n  simp [flatten_cons, getElem_cons, getElem_nil, length_cons]\n  have h1 : findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i)) (map length l).partialSums ≤ (map length l).partialSums.length := by\n    apply findIdx_le\n  have h2 : (map length l).partialSums.length = l.length + 1 := rfl\n  have h3 : findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i)) (map length l).partialSums ≤ l.length + 1 := by\n    omega\n  have h4 : findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i)) (map length l).partialSums - 1 < l.length := by\n    omega\n  cases findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i)) (map length l).partialSums with\n  | zero => simp [h4]\n  | succ j => simp [j, h4]\n\ntheorem getElem?_reverse {f b l i} : (l.reverse)[i]? = if i < (l.reverse).length then some (l.getElem (length l - 1 - i) (by omega)) else none := by\n  simp [getElem?_reverse, getElem?_nil, getElem?_cons]\ntheorem getElem?_foldr {f b l i} : (l.foldr f b)[i]? = if i < (l.foldr f b).length then some (l.foldr f b (l.drop i)) else none := by\n  simp [getElem?_foldr, getElem?_nil, getElem?_cons]\ntheorem getElem?_foldl {f b l i} : (l.foldl f b)[i]? = if i < (l.foldl f b).length then some (l.foldl f b (l.drop i)) else none := by\n  simp [getElem?_foldl, getElem?_nil, getElem?_cons]\ntheorem getElem?_partialSums {f b l i} : (l.partialSums)[i]? = if i < (l.partialSums).length then some (l.take i).sum else none := by\n  simp [getElem?_partialSums, getElem?_nil, getElem?_cons]\ntheorem getElem?_partialProds {f b l i} : (l.partialProds)[i]? = if i < (l.partialProds).length then some (l.take i).prod else none := by\n  simp [getElem?_partialProds, getElem?_nil, getElem?_cons]\ntheorem getElem?_flatten {f b l i} : (l.flatten)[i]? = if i < (l.flatten).length then some (l.getElem (findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i)) (map length l).partialSums - 1) (by\n    have h1 : findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i)) (map length l).partialSums ≤ (map length l).partialSums.length := by\n      apply findIdx_le\n    have h2 : (map length l).partialSums.length = l.length + 1 := rfl\n    have h3 : findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i)) (map length l).partialSums ≤ l.length + 1 := by\n      omega\n    have h4 : findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i)) (map length l).partialSums - 1 < l.length := by\n      omega\n    omega\n)) else none := by\n  simp [getElem?_flatten, getElem?_nil, getElem?_cons]\n\ntheorem take_reverse {f b l i} : (l.reverse).take i = reverse (l.take i) := by\n  simp [reverse_cons, take_cons, reverse_nil, take_nil]\n  induction l generalizing i with\n  | nil => simp\n  | cons x xs ih => cases i <;> simp [ih]\ntheorem take_foldr {f b l i} : (l.foldr f b).take i = l.foldr f b (l.take i) := by\n  simp [foldr, take_cons, foldr, take_nil]\n  induction l generalizing i with\n  | nil => simp\n  | cons x xs ih => cases i <;> simp [ih]\ntheorem take_foldl {f b l i} : (l.foldl f b).take i = l.foldl f b (l.take i) := by\n  simp [foldl, take_cons, foldl, take_nil]\n  induction l generalizing i with\n  | nil => simp\n  | cons x xs ih => cases i <;> simp [ih]\ntheorem take_partialSums {f b l i} : (l.partialSums).take i = (l.take i).partialSums := by\n  simp [partialSums, take_cons, partialSums, take_nil]\n  induction l generalizing i with\n  | nil => simp\n  | cons x xs ih => cases i <;> simp [ih]\ntheorem take_partialProds {f b l i} : (l.partialProds).take i = (l.take i).partialProds := by\n  simp [partialProds, take_cons, partialProds, take_nil]\n  induction l generalizing i with\n  | nil => simp\n  | cons x xs ih => cases i <;> simp [ih]\ntheorem take_flatten {f b l i} : (l.flatten).take i = l.flatten.take i := by\n  simp [flatten_cons, take_cons, take_nil]\n\n/-! Theorems about List properties (advanced) -/\ntheorem length_flatten : length (l.flatten) = (l.map length).sum := rfl\n\ntheorem head_flatten {f b l} : (l.flatten).head (by simp) = l.head (by simp) := by\n  simp [flatten_cons, head_cons, head_nil]\n\ntheorem getLast_flatten {f b l} : (l.flatten).getLast (by simp) = l.prod := by\n  simp [flatten_cons, getLast_cons, getLast_nil]\n\ntheorem getElem?_flatten {f b l i} : (l.flatten)[i]? = if i < (l.flatten).length then some (l.getElem (findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i)) (map length l).partialSums - 1) (by\n    have h1 : findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i)) (map length l).partialSums ≤ (map length l).partialSums.length := by\n      apply findIdx_le\n    have h2 : (map length l).partialSums.length = l.length + 1 := rfl\n    have h3 : findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i)) (map length l).partialSums ≤ l.length + 1 := by\n      omega\n    have h4 : findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i)) (map length l).partialSums - 1 < l.length := by\n      omega\n    omega\n)) else none := by\n  simp [getElem?_flatten, getElem?_nil, getElem?_cons]\n\ntheorem getElem_flatten {f b l i} (h : i < (l.flatten).length) : (l.flatten)[i] = l.getElem (findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i)) (map length l).partialSums - 1) (by\n    have h1 : findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i)) (map length l).partialSums ≤ (map length l).partialSums.length := by\n      apply findIdx_le\n    have h2 : (map length l).partialSums.length = l.length + 1 := rfl\n    have h3 : findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i)) (map length l).partialSums ≤ l.length + 1 := by\n      omega\n    have h4 : findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i)) (map length l).partialSums - 1 < l.length := by\n      omega\n    omega\n) := by\n  simp [getElem?_flatten, getElem?_cons, getElem?_nil]\n  have h1 : findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i)) (map length l).partialSums ≤ (map length l).partialSums.length := by\n    apply findIdx_le\n  have h2 : (map length l).partialSums.length = l.length + 1 := rfl\n  have h3 : findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i)) (map length l).partialSums ≤ l.length + 1 := by\n    omega\n  have h4 : findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i)) (map length l).partialSums - 1 < l.length := by\n    omega\n  cases findIdx (fun x => decide (x > i))